Transform phenotype data and calculate BLUEs

23 September, 2020

This script pulls the func_generate_BLUE.R function from HAPPI-GWAS to apply a Box-Cox transformation and export BLUEs for free amino acid traits, as measured in 313 individuals of the Arabidopsis RegMap panel (Angelovici et al.2013, 2016).

knitr::opts_knit$set(root.dir = "~/Documents/AA-GenomicPrediction", 
                     warning = FALSE)

library(tidyverse)
library(lme4)

Raw Data

Load raw data

# source BoxCox transformation and BLUE function from HAPPI-GWAS
source("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Angelovici-Lab/HAPPI.GWAS/master/R/func_generate_BLUE.R") 

# read in raw FAA data
raw_data <- read.csv("data/raw/aa360_raw_ratios.csv") %>%
  mutate(Line = as.factor(Line),
         population = as.factor(population))

head(raw_data) 

raw_data %>% 
  gather(key = trait,
         value = value,
         -Line,
         -population) %>% 
  ggplot(., aes(trait, value)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1, vjust = 1))

Calculate BLUEs

This function applies a Box-Cox transformation and calculates BLUEs for each trait

Check BLUEs

BLUEs <- blues_out$BLUE

# compare blues and blups 
blues_long <- BLUEs %>% 
  gather(-Line, key = trait, value = blues) %>%
  rename(IID = Line)

blues_long %>% 
  ggplot(., aes(blues)) + 
  geom_histogram() + 
  facet_wrap(~trait, scales = "free")
View(BLUEs)

Format for LDAK

Export phenotype data formatted for LDAK (plink format)


BLUEs %>%
  mutate(FID = "AtRegMap") %>% 
  rename(IID = Line) %>% 
  select(FID, IID, everything()) %>%
  filter(IID %in% blups$IID) %>% 
  head() 

BLUEs %>%
  mutate(FID = "AtRegMap") %>% 
  rename(IID = Line) %>% 
  select(FID, IID, everything()) %>%
  filter(IID %in% blups$IID) %>% # select lines with genotype data
  write.table(., "data/processed/aa360_BLUEs.txt",
              quote = FALSE, 
              row.names = FALSE)
